mso-bidi-font-family:\"Times New Roman\"; 	mso-bidi-theme-font:minor-bidi;} @page WordSection1 	{size:8.5in 11.0in; 	margin:1.0in 1.25in 1.0in 1.25in; 	mso-header-margin:.5in; 	mso-footer-margin:.5in; 	mso-paper-source:0;} div.WordSection1 	{page:WordSection1;} -->\n\n<strong>MARYSVILLE, Wash.</strong> <strong>(July 10, 2013)</strong><strong> – </strong>Northside, a leading family footwear brand, today announces a reinvestment in retail-focused initiatives in an effort to better support its\ndealers and strengthen the brand’s retail presence.\n\nThe investment is engineered around the goal of providing superior customer service, support systems and visual merchandising to Northside dealers, said Jack Wolfin, the brand’s\npresident.\n\nAs an independent, family owned and operated business, Northside owners Jeff Thayer, Bob Thayer and Jack Wolfin have implemented a new brand promise and pledge to retailers: “As the owners of the Northside brand, we are immersed in every aspect of how we touch your business. We understand that our success is a function of yours and want you to rest assured that we will continue to stand behind every Northside product,\nlong after the sale.”\n\nIn conjunction with the debut of the spring/summer 2014 line to trade audiences, Northside will implement new practices and systems to better support the company’s dealers. Efforts include extensive sales rep training, more effective point of sale materials, additional branding assets, increased owner visibility and availability, re-vamped delivery processes and accountability standards, and an overall show of appreciation with engaging\non-floor initiatives.  Not only will these efforts further the reinvestment plans, but they will also embody and\nbring to life the brand’s updated tagline: “Just for Fun.”\n\n“As the Northside brand continues to build a following in\nthe outdoor marketplace, Jeff, Bob, and I recognized that the next step towards\nsuccess is to really grow and support the programs that bring success to our\npartners,” said Wolfin. “We know that any victory we see is a result of our\ndealers’ achievements, and we want to ensure that we are doing everything\npossible to enable these partners to reach their goals, to have fun doing it,\nand to know that we have their backs. Our product isn’t changing; nor is our\nvision – we are simply making a larger effort to show our appreciation to those\nwho make our business work.”\n\nThough the Northside Promise is new for the brand, Northside\nremains committed to creating the same quality footwear that consumers have\ncome to expect. The spring/summer 2014 line will further the brand’s standard\nof on-trend, dependable shoes for the whole family at a great value.\n\nFor more information on the Northside brand and products,\nvisit <a href=\"http://www.northsideusa.com\">www.northsideusa.com</a>, and stay\ntuned for updates on the Northside Promise.\n\n<strong>About Northside</strong>\nNorthside by Triple T Trading is a quality footwear brand\nfor all-seasons, available in contemporary styles. Offering a range of styles\nfrom winter boots and trail shoes to sandals and flip-flops, Northside shoes\nare rugged, reliable and affordable for families who want to enjoy the outdoors\ntogether. Triple T Trading, the parent company for the Northside brand was\nfounded in 1985 with the goal to design, manufacture and sell well-made affordable\nfootwear. Northside by Triple T Trading is headquartered in Marysville, Wash.\nFor more information, please visit www.northsideusa.com.\n\n&nbsp;','Northside Announces New Brand Promise','Brand reinvests in retail partnerships','inherit','open','open','','21149-autosave-v1','','','2014-09-15 15:55:11','2014-09-15 15:55:11','',21149,'http://northsideusa.com/21149-autosave-v1/',0,'revision','',0),(21373,1,'2012-07-30 15:26:24','2012-07-30 15:26:24','MARYSVILLE, Wash. (July 30, 2012) &ndash; Northside, a leader in comfortable, durable and affordable outdoor and lifestyle footwear, will be introducing new styles for the whole family at Outdoor Retailer Summer Market 2012, Booth #29131. Northside&rsquo;s new footwear designs are reliable and comfortable from the trail to the river, or for kicking around town all summer.<br />\r\n<br />\r\nThe Northside brand, now 12-years-old, is a unique brand that represents quality, rugged, reliable and affordable footwear available in contemporary styles for all members of the family. Northside&rsquo;s lighthearted, down to earth branding stems from the company&rsquo;s core values, one of which identifies the importance of lasting experiences that result from families enjoying the outdoors together.<br />\r\n<br />\r\n&ldquo;We couldn&rsquo;t be happier with our new line for Spring &rsquo;13,&rdquo; said Jack Wolfin, president of Triple T Trading. &ldquo;Our designers have really taken the sport and water shoe categories to the next level with quality footwear designs that bring style and comfort to families at a reasonable price.&rdquo;<br />\r\n<br />\r\nNEW for Spring/Summer 2013:<br />\r\n<br />\r\nTRAIL / LIFESTYLE:<br />\r\n<br />\r\nNorthside Men&rsquo;s Caldera &ndash; SRP $35<br />\r\nThe Caldera was designed with a suede and mesh upper making this day hiker rugged yet comfortable. An abrasion resistant PVC heel and toe guard and TPR traction outsole provide support and protection. Sizes M 8 &ndash; 13. Available in Stone/Yellow.<br />\r\n<br />\r\nNorthside Women&rsquo;s Kiona LTC &ndash; SRP $26.50<br />\r\nReady for the trail, the women&rsquo;s Kiona LTC was developed with a combination of ultra-lightweight soft shell and breathable mesh to keep feet comfortable and dry on the go. The compression molded EVA midsole paired with the high traction outsole makes this sporty shoe perfect for road to trail. Sizes W 6 &ndash; 10. Available in Black/Purple and Grey/Fuchsia<br />\r\n<br />\r\nNorthside Kids Cheyenne / Cheyenne Jr. &ndash; SRP $14.50<br />\r\nThese durable little hikers offer a nice lightweight fit and feel. The suede and mesh upper provides breathability while the high traction outsole gives sure footing for exploring the outdoors. Cushioned for a comfort with a quick lacing system (or Velcro) for the perfect fit. Sizes: Toddler 5 &ndash; 10, Boys 4-7, Girls 11-5, Kids 11-3. Available in Tan/Aqua and Taupe/Mango.<br />\r\n<br />\r\nNorthside Del Rio LTC &ndash; SRP $20 - $40<br />\r\nFeaturing an all-new urban casual design, the Del Rio LTC is styled for everyday wear with the outdoors in mind. A unique combination of breathable mesh materials, a fixed stretch neoprene tongue and a nylon Speed Lace System, the Del Rio LTC is designed to mold to your foot for long-term lightweight comfort. Available in men&rsquo;s, women&rsquo;s and children&rsquo;s specific sizes and colors.<br />\r\n<br />\r\nNorthside Women&rsquo;s Del Sol LTC &ndash; SRP $20<br />\r\nThe Women&rsquo;s Del Sol is the perfect mix of urban style and everyday comfort. The breathable mesh sock construction and Speed Lacing System make the Del Sol a hip option for work and play.&nbsp; Sizes W 6 &ndash; 10. Available in Grey/Pink, Brown/Purple and Grey/Green.<br />\r\n<br />\r\n<br />\r\nWATER:<br />\r\n<br />\r\nNorthside Raging River &ndash; SRP $50<br />\r\nThis all-purpose water shoe features a contour cushioned perforated EVA insole and TPR traction outsole with drainage ports to allow easy water flow. The comfortable sock constructed upper and Drawstring Speed Lacing System allow for perfect fit. A quick-dry mesh upper ensures that feet won&rsquo;t be left soggy. Sizes M 8 &ndash; 13, W 6 - 10. Available for men in Black/Green and Grey/Yellow,<br />\r\nand for women in Grey/Light Blue and Grey/Fuchsia.<br />\r\n<br />\r\nNorthside Burke II &ndash; SRP $15 - $30<br />\r\nPossibly the most popular shoe in the Northside Sport Line, the Burke II is the refined version of it&rsquo;s predecessor. Developed with a contour cushioned brushed EVA insole and TPR outsole for sure-step and foot protection. This amphibious shoe features waterproof PU and EVA lined upper for extra comfort and the Elastic Drawstring Lacing System and Lace Keeper. Available in men&rsquo;s, women&rsquo;s and children&rsquo;s specific sizes and colors.<br />\r\n<br />\r\nNorthside shoes are available at more than 500 retailers and major online stores nationwide. Northside shoes typically retail from $29 to $69.<br />\r\n<br />\r\nAbout Verde PR &amp; Consulting<br />\r\nWith offices in Durango and Boulder, Colo. and Jackson, Wyo., Verde PR &amp; Consulting is a full-service traditional and digital public relations, marketing, branding, and consulting agency, with an emphasis in sustainability. Verde&rsquo;s clients are rooted in the outdoor, bike, and snowsports industries, as well as the health and wellness and Lifestyles of Health and Sustainability (LOHAS) markets. For more, visit: http://www.verdepr.com.<br />\r\n<br />\r\nAbout Northside<br />\r\nNorthside by Triple T Trading is a quality footwear brand for all-seasons, available in contemporary styles. Offering a range of styles from winter boots and trail shoes to sandals and flip-flops, Northside shoes are rugged, reliable and affordable for families who want to enjoy the outdoors together. Triple T Trading, the parent company for the Northside brand was founded in 1985 with the goal to design, manufacture and sell well-made affordable footwear. Northside by Triple T Trading is headquartered in Marysville, Wash. For more information, please visit www.northsideusa.com.','Northside brings new outdoor footwear for the whole family  to Outdoor Retailer Summer Market 2012','','draft','closed','closed','','northside-brings-new-outdoor-footwear-for-the-whole-family-to-outdoor-retailer-summer-market-2012-2','','','2014-09-15 15:58:37','2014-09-15 15:58:37','',0,'http://northsideusa.com/northside-brings-new-outdoor-footwear-for-the-whole-family-to-outdoor-retailer-summer-market-2012-2/',0,'post','',0),(21381,8,'2014-09-26 22:45:32','2014-09-26 22:45:32','It’s Saturday morning and your kids are rolling out of bed at 5 a.m. with energy you still won’t match after six cups of coffee. But when you\'re aptly caffeinated and ask the riled up little ones where they want to hike today, you’re met with groans and complaints: “Hiking is boring!” “I hate hiking.” “Not again!”\r\n\r\n<span style=\"color: #800000;\"><strong><a style=\"color: #800000;\" title=\"NORTHSIDE KIDS ACTIVE SHOES\" href=\"http://northsideusa.com/shoes/category/kids-active/\" target=\"_blank\">FOR YOUR GROWING HIKER: NORTHSIDE KIDS\' ACTIVE SHOES</a></strong></span>\r\n\r\nBut you know that hiking isn’t boring and more importantly, that your kiddos need exercise ASAP. Here are a few tips for getting them outside and in the hills.<a href=\"http://northsideusa.com/2014/wp-content/uploads/2014/09/1866603320_16dd6e77b2_o.jpg\"><img class=\"alignnone size-full wp-image-21382\" src=\"http://northsideusa.com/2014/wp-content/uploads/2014/09/1866603320_16dd6e77b2_o.jpg\" alt=\"hiking-with-kids\" width=\"3872\" height=\"2592\" /></a><i>Photo credit: Mike Barlow/Flickr</i>\r\n\r\n<strong>Make the hike into a game</strong>\r\n\r\n“I spy\" is a perfect trail game. Make and bring along bingo boards that list possible finds, so if the kids unearth five items that are listed in a row, they win a prize. To keep them interested throughout the hike, list easy treasures (hearing a bird whistle, finding a heart-shaped rock, collecting six pinecones) and mix in some less likely items (seeing a deer, finding an arrowhead, spying a hawk).\r\n\r\nThe prize at the end? An extra scoop of ice cream or a really cool rock found at the local nature store that can be traded between each hike’s winner.<a href=\"http://northsideusa.com/2014/wp-content/uploads/2014/09/8282458845_c021f29a6e_o.jpg\"><img class=\"alignnone size-full wp-image-21385\" src=\"http://northsideusa.com/2014/wp-content/uploads/2014/09/8282458845_c021f29a6e_o.jpg\" alt=\"snack spot\" width=\"3000\" height=\"2417\" /></a><em>Photo credit: dolanh/Flickr</em>\r\n\r\n<strong>Bribery</strong>\r\n\r\nAs much as we’d like to be, most of us aren’t above blatant bribery. Whether it’s feeding them throughout the hike with (mostly M&amp;M-filled) trail mix, a promise of a post-hike frozen treat or getting an extra 30 minutes with mom’s iPad at night, enticement works. Often they’ll forget about the bribery after a few steps into the trail and will just enjoy being outside.<a href=\"http://northsideusa.com/2014/wp-content/uploads/2014/09/532314966_75c4c291ff_o.jpg\"><img class=\"alignnone size-full wp-image-21383\" src=\"http://northsideusa.com/2014/wp-content/uploads/2014/09/532314966_75c4c291ff_o.jpg\" alt=\"532314966_75c4c291ff_o\" width=\"800\" height=\"649\" /></a><i>Photo credit: Jonf728/Flickr</i>\r\n\r\n<strong>Have a goal</strong>\r\n\r\nAlthough many hikes top out with beautiful views, some younger kids just don’t care how gorgeous the mountain in the distance is, or the amazing fall colors. Instead, have something they can look forward to on the hike. On a hot day, take them to a hike that ends at a lake perfect for a refreshing swim. Or tempt them with the perfect hollow rock that doubles as a secret fort. Or, as a fall-appropriate adventure, hike them to apple trees. There, they can eat their fill of the sweet, juicy apples while you pack them in your bag for apple pie baking later.<a href=\"http://northsideusa.com/2014/wp-content/uploads/2014/09/2397012858_277b3f403a_o.jpg\"><img class=\"alignnone size-full wp-image-21384\" src=\"http://northsideusa.com/2014/wp-content/uploads/2014/09/2397012858_277b3f403a_o.jpg\" alt=\"2397012858_277b3f403a_o\" width=\"2206\" height=\"1471\" /></a><em>Photo credit: woodleywonderworks/Flickr</em>\r\n\r\n<strong>Incorporate a project</strong>\r\n\r\nIf your child is <em>still </em>not excited about the trek through the woods, associate it with something that he or she is interested in. For example, if your 10 year old likes arts and crafts, have him collect flowers, pretty leaves and feathers to create a scrapbook or poster later. Or, if your eight year old enjoys science, make sure to point out the bird’s nest you see and have her take photos with your iPhone. Then, later, you can research what kind of bird those eggs belong to.\r\n\r\nDo you have tricks to get your kids to go on a hike? Tell us in the comments.','How to Get Your Kids to Hike','','publish','open','open','','how-to-get-your-kids-to-hike','','','2014-09-26 22:46:51','2014-09-26 22:46:51','',0,'http://northsideusa.com/?p=21381',0,'post','',0),(21380,0,'2012-07-30 15:26:24','1970-01-01 00:00:00','MARYSVILLE, Wash. (July 30, 2012) &ndash; Northside, a leader in comfortable, durable and affordable outdoor and lifestyle footwear, will be introducing new styles for the whole family at Outdoor Retailer Summer Market 2012, Booth #29131. Northside&rsquo;s new footwear designs are reliable and comfortable from the trail to the river, or for kicking around town all summer.<br />\r\n<br />\r\nThe Northside brand, now 12-years-old, is a unique brand that represents quality, rugged, reliable and affordable footwear available in contemporary styles for all members of the family. Northside&rsquo;s lighthearted, down to earth branding stems from the company&rsquo;s core values, one of which identifies the importance of lasting experiences that result from families enjoying the outdoors together.<br />\r\n<br />\r\n&ldquo;We couldn&rsquo;t be happier with our new line for Spring &rsquo;13,&rdquo; said Jack Wolfin, president of Triple T Trading. &ldquo;Our designers have really taken the sport and water shoe categories to the next level with quality footwear designs that bring style and comfort to families at a reasonable price.&rdquo;<br />\r\n<br />\r\nNEW for Spring/Summer 2013:<br />\r\n<br />\r\nTRAIL / LIFESTYLE:<br />\r\n<br />\r\nNorthside Men&rsquo;s Caldera &ndash; SRP $35<br />\r\nThe Caldera was designed with a s